# React SuperAdmin Project Structure & Development

## Project Overview
This is a monorepo with pnpm workspaces containing:
- `packages/core`: Core framework with TypeScript, React hooks, contexts, and utilities
- `packages/web`: Web admin interface using Vite, React, Tailwind CSS
- `docs`: Docusaurus documentation site

## Development Commands
- Use `pnpm dev` to start development (runs web package)
- Use `pnpm docs:dev` to start documentation development server
- Use `pnpm docs:build` to build documentation
- Use `pnpm docs:serve` to serve built documentation locally
- Use `pnpm firebase:deploy` to deploy documentation to Firebase Hosting
- Use `pnpm build` to build both packages
- Use `pnpm build:core` or `pnpm build:web` for individual packages

## Key Patterns
- Components use PascalCase naming (e.g., DataTable, ResourceForm)
- Hooks use camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., useAuth, useFilters)
- Core package exports reusable framework code
- Web package imports from core and provides admin interface
- Both packages use TypeScript with strict mode

## File Organization
- Core package: `packages/core/src/components/`, `packages/core/src/contexts/`, `packages/core/src/hooks/`, `packages/core/src/types/`, `packages/core/src/utils/`
- Web package: `packages/web/src/components/crud/`, `packages/web/src/components/forms/`, `packages/web/src/components/layout/`, `packages/web/src/components/ui/`
- Documentation: `docs/docs/` for content, `docs/src/` for custom components
- Use relative imports within packages, package imports between packages

## Technology Stack
- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Vite for web package build tool
- Docusaurus for documentation
- pnpm as package manager with workspace support
- Firebase Hosting for documentation deployment
